%N A396636 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of at-most-k-furcating labeled histories that can be constructed for n labeled leaves, 2<=k<=n, if simultaneous branching events are allowed.
%C A396636 Labeled histories with simultaneity for at-most-k-furcating trees can be extended to n=1, with T(1,k)=1. They can also be extended to k>n, with T(n,k)=T(n,n) for k>n.
%H A396636 Emily H. Dickey and Noah A. Rosenberg, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.dam.2026.04.032">Labeled histories and maximally probable labeled topologies with multifurcation</a>, Discr. Appl. Math. 391 (2026), 192-203. See Table 2.
